    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - LIFT AXLE SYSTEMS - CONTROLS - IN-CAB CONTROLS</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="hl14019072" svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
        <title>IN-CAB CONTROLS</title>
        <para>In this configuration all of the axle controls are located on a floor mounted pedestal next to the
            driver's seat (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f14019y">FIGURE 25</hotlnk>). The external panel located at the rear of the cab contains no
            controls and acts only as a pass-thru for the system air lines.
        </para>
        <specpara>
            <important>
                <para>On trucks with multiple lift axles the controls are located as follows. The controls for the lift
                    axle closest to the front of the truck are located closest to the top of the pedestal. The controls
                    for the lift axle furthest from the front of the truck are located furthest from the top of the
                    pedestal.
                </para>
            </important>
        </specpara>
